          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>  </p>
              <p>1 fol.; Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: H. S. 183; Qurʾānic Text: 77:9-77:50; 5 lines per page; Dimensions: 205 x 145mm; Script style: kūfī.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This entry is based on the catalogue of Fehmi E. Karatay (1888-1968). Currently we do not have access to the images. With exceptions, the catalogue does not contain precise information on the distribution of the text throughout the pages. For this reason, only fol. 1 is given. </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>Karatay (1962) describes the manuscripts as follows, p. 26: "77 H. S. 183. Kur’an yaprağı. Parşömen. 145mm boy ve 205mm eninde tek yaprak. Sahifede kûfî yazı ve altınla 140mm uzunl.[uğunda] 5 satır. Tahminen V. asırda yazılmıştır. Bu yaprak Mursalāt (77) suresinin 9. ayetinden aynı surenin sonuna kadardır."</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>This can be translated as follows: "77 H. S. 183. A leaf of the Qurʾān. Parchment. One leaf of 145 mm height and 205 mm width. The text area written with Kufic script in gold ink [contains] 5 lines measuring 140 mm. Probably copied during the 5th century. This leaf begins with the Q 77:9 (Sūra al-Mursalāt) and continues until the end of the of the same sūra.”</p>
            </summary>
